      • EncryptAs

        public boolean EncryptAs(java.lang.String dst,
                java.lang.String upswd,
                java.lang.String opswd,
                int perm,
                int method,
                byte[] id)
        encrypt document and save as the document to another file.
        this method need premium license.
        Overrides:
        EncryptAs in class Document
        Parameters:
        dst - path to save， same as path parameter of SaveAs.
        upswd - user password, can be null.
        opswd - owner password, can be null.
        perm - permission to set, same as GetPermission() method.
        bit 1-2 reserved
        bit 3(0x4) print
        bit 4(0x8) modify
        bit 5(0x10) extract text or image
        others: see PDF reference
        method - reserved, currently only AES with V=4 and R=4 mode can be working.
        id - must be 32 bytes for file ID. it is divided to 2 array in native library, as each 16 bytes.
        Returns:
        true or false.

      • GetSignByteRange

        public int[] GetSignByteRange()
        get byte ranges from PDF file, to get digest.
        this method valid in professional or premium version.
        Overrides:
        GetSignByteRange in class Document
        Returns:
        an integer pair array, to record byte ranges.
        each pair describing a range to digest.
        1st element of pair is offset.
        2nd element of pair is length.

      • CheckSignByteRange

        public int CheckSignByteRange()
        check object defined in signature("Data" entry), is in byte ranges defined in signature. this method valid in professional or premium version.
        to ensure PDF file modified, mostly you shall(Adobe Standard):
        1. invoke this method first.
        2. if succeeded, then get signature contents(see GetSignContents).
        3. decode public key from contents(see GetSignContents).
        4. decode encrypted digest from contents.
        5. decrypt digest.1 using public key, for step 4.
        6. calculate digest.2 by yourself, using byte ranges(GetSignByteRange).
        7. check digest.1 == digest.2
        Overrides:
        CheckSignByteRange in class Document
        Returns:

        -1: unknown or not defined in signature.
        0: check failed, means modified.
        1: check succeeded, means no new objects after signature.
